### API Test File for Nyamula Logistics Auth Module
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = your_token_here

### 1. Sign Up as Transporter
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Transporter",
  "email": "john.transport@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "companyName": "Fast Wheels Logistics",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "role": "transporter"
}

### 2. Sign Up as Cargo Owner
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Jane Cargo",
  "email": "jane.cargo@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "companyName": "Global Trading Co",
  "phoneNumber": "+0987654321",
  "role": "cargo-owner"
}

### 3. Login as Transporter
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.transport@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Login as Cargo Owner
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.cargo@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Get Profile (Protected - requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Verify Token (Protected - requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Test Invalid Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

